The paper deals with the computational complexity analysis of genetic programming, which falls under the category of evolutionary algorithms. The paper focuses on two model problems, ORDER and MAJORITY, which are related to graph theory and machine learning, respectively. Therefore, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
